f-WTCServer_WTCLocalTuxDom-a-AccessPoint: The connection principal name used to identify this local Tuxedo access point when attempting to establish a session connection with remote Tuxedo access points. Note that the AccessPointId must match the corresponding DOMAINID in the *DM_REMOTE_DOMAINS section of your Tuxedo DMCONFIG file.
f-WTCServer_WTCRemoteTuxDom-a-AccessPoin: The connection principal name used to identify this remote domain access point when attempting to establish a session connection to local Tuxedo access points. This value must be globally unique among all interconnected Tuxedo and WTC Domains.
f-WTCServer_WTCRemoteTuxDom-a-AclPolicy-: The inbound access control list (ACL) policy toward requests from a remote Tuxedo access point.  The allowed values are Local or Global. Local causes the local Tuxedo access point modifies the identity of service requests received from a given remote Tuxedo access point to the principal name specified in the local principal name for a given remote Tuxedo access point. Global causes tocal Tuxedo access point passes the service request with no change in identity. Note that if Interoperate is set to Yes, the AclPolicy is ignored.

f-SingletonService-a-AdditionalMigration: A migratable service could fail to come up on every possible configured server. This attribute controls how many further attempts, after the service has failed on every server at least once, should be tried. Note that each attempt specified here indicates another full circuit of migrations amongst all the configured servers. So for a 3-server cluster, and a value of 2, a total of 4 additional migrations will be attempted (the original server is never a valid destination).
f-WTCServer_WTCRemoteTuxDom-a-AllowAnony: Specifies whether the anonymous user is allowed to access remote Tuxedo services. Note that if the anonymous user is allowed to access Tuxedo, the default AppKey will be used for TpUsrFile and LDAP AppKey plug-ins. Interaction with the Custom AppKey plug-in depends on the design of the Custom AppKey generator.
f-WTCServer_WTCtBridgeGlobal-a-AllowNonS: Specifies whether non-standard data types are allowed to pass through this Tuxedo queuing bridge. A value of NO means that non standard types are rejected and placed onto a specified error location; a value of YES means that non-standard types are placed on the target location as BLOBs with a tag indicating the original type. Standard types are ASCII text (TextMessage, STRING) or BLOB (BytesMessage, CARRAY).
a-AltDescriptorDir-help: The location of this application's configuration area. This directory can contain alternate descriptor files. If the alternate descriptor directory is a relative path, it is resolved relative to InstallDir if InstallDir is not null; otherwise, it is resolved relative to the domain root.
a-AltDescriptorPath-help: A path on the file system for the application descriptor for this application. If null, the usual location within the EAR is used (META-INF/application.xml).
a-AltWLSDescriptorPath-help: A path on the file system for the WebLogic Server-specific application descriptor for this application. If null, the usual location within the EAR file is used.
a-AppKey-help: Specifies the type of AppKey plug-in used.  The allowed values are TpUsrFile, LDAP, and Custom.  TpUsrFile is the default plug-in and uses an imported Tuxedo TPUSR file to provide user security information. The LDAP plug-in utilizes an embedded LDAP server to provide user security information; the user record must define the Tuxedo UID and GID information in the description field. The Custom plug-in provides the ability to write your own AppKey generator class to provide the security information required by Tuxedo.

f-WTCServer_WTCLocalTuxDom-a-ConnectionP: The conditions under which this local Tuxedo access point establishes a session connection with a remote Tuxedo access point. ON_DEMAND means that a connection is attempted only when requested by either a client request to a remote service or an administrative connect command. ON_STARTUP means that a domain gateway attempts to establish a connection with its remote Tuxedo access points at gateway server initialization time. Remote services (services advertised in JNDI by the domain gateway for this local access point) are advertised only if a connection is successfully established to that remote Tuxedo access point. If there is no active connection to a remote Tuxedo access point, then the remote services are suspended. By default, this connection policy retries failed connections every 60 seconds. Use the MaxRetry and RetryInterval values to specify application specific values. INCOMING_ONLY means that a domain gateway does not attempt an initial connection to remote Tuxedo access points at startup and remote services are initially suspended. The domain gateway is available for incoming connections from remote Tuxedo access points and remote services are advertised when the domain gateway for this local Tuxedo access point receives an incoming connection. Connection retry processing is not allowed.
f-WTCServer_WTCRemoteTuxDom-a-Connection: The conditions under which this remote Tuxedo access point establishes a session connection with a local Tuxedo access point. ON_DEMAND means that a connection is attempted only when requested by either a client request to a remote service or an administrative connect command. ON_STARTUP means that a domain gateway attempts to establish a connection with its remote Tuxedo access points at gateway server initialization time. Remote services (services advertised in JNDI by the domain gateway for this local Tuxedo access point) are advertised only if a connection is successfully established to that remote Tuxedo access point. If there is no active connection to a remote Tuxedo access point, then the remote services are suspended. By default, this connection policy retries failed connections every 60 seconds. Use the MaxRetry and RetryInterval attributes to specify application specific values. INCOMING_ONLY means that a domain gateway does not attempt an initial connection to remote Tuxedo access points at startup and remote services are initially suspended. The domain gateway is available for incoming connections from remote Tuxedo access points and remote services are advertised when the domain gateway for this local Tuxedo access point receives an incoming connection. Connection retry processing is not allowed. LOCAL specifies that the remote domain connection policy is explicitly defaulted to the local domain ConnectionPolicy attribute value.

f-WTCServer_WTCRemoteTuxDom-a-KeepAliveW: Indicates whether this remote Tuxedo access point requires the acknowledgement of Application Level Keep Alive. A value of 0 indicates that application-level Keep Alive is not enabled for the access point but the access point acknowledges if a heartbeat is received. A value greater than 0 indicates that application-level Keep Alive is enabled and the value indicates the amount of idle time, in milliseconds rounded to the nearest second, allowed before WebLogic Tuxedo Connector marks the connection as failed if the heartbeat is not acknowledged.

f-StartupClass-a-LoadBeforeAppDeployment: Specifies whether the targeted servers load and run this startup class before activating JMS and JDBC services and before starting deployment for applications and EJBs. If you enable this feature for a startup class, a server loads and runs the startup class before the deployment prepare phase. At this point, JMS and JDBC services are not yet available. (Deployment for applications and EJBs consists of three phases: prepare, admin and activate.)

The only way to change the plan staging mode is to undeploy and then redeploy the application. This attribute overrides the server's plan staging mode.

f-WTCServer_WTCLocalTuxDom-a-PrivateKeyA: The string alias used to store and retrieve the Local Tuxedo access point's private key in the keystore. This private key is associated with the Local Tuxedo access point's digital certificate.
f-WTCServer_WTCLocalTuxDom-a-PrivateKeyP: The encrypted passphrase used to retrieve the Local Tuxedo access point's private key from the keystore. This passphrase is assigned to the private key when it is generated.
a-PurgeResourceFromCheckpointIntervalSec: Purge Resource From Checkpoint Interval Seconds
a-RedirectStderrToServerLogEnabled-label: Redirect Stderr To Server Log Enabled
a-RedirectStdoutToServerLogEnabled-label: Redirect Stdout To Server Log Enabled
a-RejectEqualOrContainReverseUsername-la: Reject Equal Or Contain Reverse Username
a-RemoteAccessPoint-help: The name of the remote access point to which this password applies.
a-RemoteAccessPointList-help: The comma-separated failover list that identifies the remote domain access points through which resources are imported.
a-RemoteMBEncoding-help: The default encoding name of sending MBSTRING data.
f-WTCServer_WTCExport-a-RemoteName-help: The remote name of this service. Note that if not specified, the ResourceName value is used.
f-WTCServer_WTCImport-a-RemoteName-help: The remote name of this service. Note that if not specified, the ResourceName value is used.
a-RemotePassword-help: The remote password used to authenticate connections between the local access point and remote access point. Note that this password is used to authenticate connections between the local Tuxedo access point identified by LocalAccessPoint and the remote Tuxedo access point identified by RemoteAccessPoint.
a-RemotePasswordIV-help: The initialization vector used to encrypt the remote password.
f-WTCServer_WTCtBridgeRedirect-a-ReplyQ-: The name of the JMS queue used specifically for synchronous calls to a Tuxedo service. The response is returned to the JMS ReplyQ.
a-ReplyToSAFRemoteContextName-label: Reply To SAF Remote Context Name
f-WTCServer_WTCExport-a-ResourceName-hel: The name used to identify this exported service. The combination of ResourceName and LocalAccessPoint must be unique within defined Exports. This allows you to define unique configurations having the same ResourceName.
f-WTCServer_WTCImport-a-ResourceName-hel: The name used to identify this imported service. Note that this name must be unique within defined Imports. This allows you to define unique configurations having the same Remote Name.
f-WTCServer_WTCtBridgeGlobal-a-Retries-h: The number of attempts to redirect a message before this Tuxedo queuing bridge places the message in the specified error location and logs an error.  Must be between 0 and 2147483647.
f-WTCServer_WTCtBridgeGlobal-a-RetryDela: The minimum number of milliseconds this Tuxedo queuing bridge waits before redirecting a message after a failure. Must be between 0 and 2147483647; the default value is 10.
f-WTCServer_WTCLocalTuxDom-a-RetryInterv: The number of seconds that this local Tuxedo access point waits between automatic connection attempts to remote Tuxedo access points. Use this only when the ConnectionPolicy value is set to ON_STARTUP  The default value is 60.
f-WTCServer_WTCRemoteTuxDom-a-RetryInter: The number of seconds that this remote Tuxedo access point waits between automatic connection attempts to local Tuxedo access points. Use this only when the ConnectionPolicy value is set to ON_STARTUP  Note that when the ConnectionPolicy value is LOCAL, the RetryInterval value from the local Tuxedo access point is used. When the ConnectionPolicy value is ON_STARTUP, a value of -1 indicates 60..
a-RollbackLocalTxUponConnClose-label: Rollback Local Tx Upon Conn Close
a-SameSiteFilterSecureChannelRequired-la: Same Site Filter Secure Channel Required
a-SameSiteFilterUserAgentRegEx-label: Same Site Filter User Agent Reg Ex
a-SecondsToTrustAnIdlePoolConnection-lab: Seconds To Trust An Idle Pool Connection
f-WTCServer_WTCLocalTuxDom-a-Security-he: The type of application security enforced. NONE means that no security is used. APP_PW means that password security is enforced when a connection is established from a remote domain; the application password is defined in the WTCResourcesMBean. DM_PW means that the domain password security is enforced when a connection is established from a remote domain; the domain password is defined in the WTCPasswordsMBean.
f-Application-a-SecurityDDModel-help:
The security model that is used to secure a deployed module.

To set this value, you can use the weblogic.Deployer command-line tool, the Deployment Assistant in the Administration Console, the WebLogic Scripting Tool (WLST), or another JMX client. If you deploy a module using one of the previously mentioned tools and you do not specify a security model value, the module is secured with the security realm's default model. If you deploy a module by modifying the domain's config.xml file and restarting the server, and if you do not specify a security model value for the module in config.xml, the module is secured with the DDOnly model, which is the default value of this AppDeploymentMBean attribute.
a-SelfTuningThreadPoolSizeMax-label: Self Tuning Thread Pool Size Max
a-SelfTuningThreadPoolSizeMin-label: Self Tuning Thread Pool Size Min
a-ServerGroupTargetingLimits-keyHelp: The name of the server group
a-ServerGroupTargetingLimits-valueHelp: The dynamic cluster targets for the server group
a-ServerLoggingBridgeAtRootLoggerEnabled: Server Logging Bridge At Root Logger Enabled
a-ServerLoggingBridgeUseParentLoggersEna: Server Logging Bridge Use Parent Loggers Enabled
a-ServerPrivateKeyPassPhraseEncrypted-la: Server Private Key Pass Phrase Encrypted
a-ServiceProviderSingleLogoutRedirectUri: Service Provider Single Logout Redirect URI
a-SnmpAccessForUserMBeansEnabled-label: SNMP Access For User MBeans Enabled
a-SocketBufferSizeAsChunkSize-label: Socket Buffer Size As Chunk Size
a-SourceAccessPoint-help: The name of the local or remote access point where the source is located.
f-WTCServer_WTCtBridgeRedirect-a-SourceN: The name of a source queue or service. Specifies a JMS queue name, a Tuxedo queue name, or the name of a Tuxedo service.
a-SourcePath-help: The path to the source of the deployable unit on the Administration Server.
f-Application-a-SourcePath-help: The path to the source of the deployable unit on the Administration Server. If the source path is relative, it is resolved relative to InstallDir/app if InstallDir is not null; otherwise, it is resolved relative to the domain root.
f-WTCServer_WTCtBridgeRedirect-a-SourceQ: The name of the Qspace for a source location.
a-SslClientIdentityPassPhraseEncrypted-l: SSL Client Identity Pass Phrase Encrypted
f-WTCServer_WTCLocalTuxDom-a-SslProtocol: The protocol version of the SSL connection this local access point uses when establishing a SSL connection.
f-WTCServer_WTCRemoteTuxDom-a-SslProtoco: The protocol version of the SSL connection this remote access point uses when establishing a SSL connection with specific local access point.
a-SsoSigningKeyPassPhraseEncrypted-label: SSO Signing Key Pass Phrase Encrypted
a-StagingMode-help: Specifies whether a deployment's files are copied from a source on the Administration Server to the Managed Server's staging area during application preparation. Staging mode for an application can only be set the first time the application is deployed. Once the staging mode for an application is set, it cannot be changed while the application is configured in the domain. The only way to change the staging mode is to undeploy and then redeploy the application. This attribute overrides the server's staging mode.
a-StartupTimeoutNumOfThreadDump-label: Startup Timeout Num Of Thread Dump
a-StaticGroupDNsfromMemberDNFilter-label: Static Group D Nsfrom Member DN Filter
a-StuckThreadDiagnosticImageNotification: Stuck Thread Diagnostic Image Notification Enabled
a-StuckThreadThreadDumpActionCount-label: Stuck Thread Thread Dump Action Count
a-StuckThreadThreadDumpActionDelaySecond: Stuck Thread Thread Dump Action Delay Seconds
a-StuckThreadThreadDumpActionEnabled-lab: Stuck Thread Thread Dump Action Enabled
a-SyncFilterOnlyClientCertRequests-label: Sync Filter Only Client Cert Requests
a-Target-help: The servers or clusters to which the deployment is deployed.
f-WTCServer_WTCtBridgeRedirect-a-TargetA: The name of the local or remote access point where the target is located.
f-WTCServer_WTCtBridgeRedirect-a-TargetN: The name of the target queue or service. Specifies a JMS queue name, a Tuxedo queue name, or the name of a Tuxedo service.
f-WTCServer_WTCtBridgeRedirect-a-TargetQ: The name of the Qspace for a target location.
f-WTCServer_WTCtBridgeGlobal-a-Timeout-h: The number of timeout seconds for an entire redirection when this Tuxedo queuing bridge places a message on the target location. A value of 0 specifies an infinite wait and the default value is 60.
a-TlogWriteWhenDeterminerExistsEnabled-l: TLOG Write When Determiner Exists Enabled
f-WTCServer_WTCRemoteTuxDom-a-TpUsrFile-:
The full path to the user password file containing UID/GID information. (This field is only relevant if you specify TpUsrFile as the AppKey Generator.)

Note: This file is generated by the Tuxedo tpusradd utility on the remote Tuxedo domain specified by the remote Tuxedo access point. A copy of this file must be available in your WebLogic Tuxedo Connector environment to provide correct authorization, authentication, and auditing.
f-WTCServer_WTCResources-a-TpUsrFile-hel: The full path to the TPUSR file, which contains Tuxedo UID/GID information. Note that this file is generated by the Tuxedo tpusradd utility on the remote Tuxedo domain.
f-WTCServer_WTCtBridgeGlobal-a-Transacti: Specifies whether this Tuxedo queuing bridge should use transactions when retrieving messages from a source location and when placing messages on a target location. A value of YES means that transactions are used for both operations; a value of NO means that transactions are not used for either operation.
a-TranslateFML-help: The type of XML/FML translation.  NO indicates that no data translation is performed. FLAT indicates that the message payload is transformed using the WebLogic Tuxedo Connector translator. WLXT indicates that translation is performed by the XML-to-non-XML WebLogic XML Translator (WLXT).
a-TransportLayerSecurityKeyPassPhraseEnc: Transport Layer Security Key Pass Phrase Encrypted
a-TriggerTruncationStackFrameDepthAfterT: Trigger Truncation Stack Frame Depth After Trigger
a-TriggerTruncationStackFrameTriggerDept: Trigger Truncation Stack Frame Trigger Depth
f-WTCServer_WTCLocalTuxDom-a-TrustKeySto: The path and file name of the trust keystore. The path name must either be absolute or relative to where the server was booted. This file name is only used if KeyStores is "Custom Stores".
a-TrustKeyStorePassPhraseEncrypted-label: Trust Key Store Pass Phrase Encrypted
f-WTCServer_WTCLocalTuxDom-a-TrustKeySto: he trust keystore's passphrase. If empty or null, then the keystore will be opened without a passphrase. This attribute is only used if KeyStores is "Custom Stores".
f-WTCServer_WTCtBridgeGlobal-a-TuxErrorQ: The name of the Tuxedo queue used to store a message that cannot be redirected to a Tuxedo/Q source queue. If not specified, all messages not redirected are lost. If the message cannot be placed into the TuxErrorQueue, an error is logged and the message is lost. Note that this queue is in the same queue space as the source queue.
a-TuxFactory-help: The name of the Tuxedo connection factory. The default value is tuxedo.services.TuxedoConnection.
a-TuxToJmsPriorityMap-help: The mapping of priorities to map from Tuxedo to JMS. The default JMS To Tux Priority Map is: 1-10:0 | 11-20:1 | 21-30:2 | 31-40:3| 41-50:4| 51-60:5 | 61-70:6 | 71-80:7 | 81-90:8 | 91-100:9.
a-TuxedoGidKw-help: The keyword for Tuxedo GID (Group ID) used in the WlsUser when using the Tuxedo migration utility tpmigldap. This keyword is only relevant if you specify LDAP as the AppKey Generator. The keyword is used to find Tuxedo GID in the user record in the embedded LDAP database.
a-TuxedoUidKw-help: The keyword for Tuxedo UID (User ID) used in the WlsUser when using the Tuxedo migration utility tpmigldap. This keyword is only relevant if you specify LDAP as the AppKey Generator. The keyword is used to find Tuxedo UID in the user record in the embedded LDAP database.
a-TwoWayTLSRequiredForAdminClients-label: Two Way TLS Required For Admin Clients
a-Untargeted-help: Only relevant for deployments in resource group templates. This flag, when specified as true, indicates that the application deployment must not be deployed in the referring partition.
a-UseConcurrentQueueForRequestManager-la: Use Concurrent Queue For Request Manager
a-UseEnhancedPriorityQueueForRequestMana: Use Enhanced Priority Queue For Request Manager
a-UseNonSecureAddressesForDomain-label: Use Non Secure Addresses For Domain

a-UseRetrievedUserNameAsPrincipal-label: Use Retrieved User Name As Principal
a-UseSAFTimeToLiveDefault-label: Use SAF Time To Live Default
f-WTCServer_WTCLocalTuxDom-a-UseSSL-help: Specifies if the connection initiated or accepted by this Local Tuxedo access point uses SSL on top of its transport layer. Note that if the SDP transport is configured for this access point, the configured value of this attribute is ignored and off is used.
a-UseTokenGroupsForGroupMembershipLookup: Use Token Groups For Group Membership Lookup
f-WTCServer_WTCtBridgeGlobal-a-UserId-he: The user identity for all messages handled by this Tuxedo queuing bridge for ACL checks when security is configured. All messages assume this identity until the security/authentication contexts are passed between the subsystems. Until the security contexts are passed, there is no secure method to identify who generated a message received from the source location. The user argument may be specified as either a user name or a user identification number (uid).
f-Application-a-ValidateDDSecurityData-h: Whether to validate the deployment descriptor security data.  Not used in modern versions of WebLogic Server.
a-ViewTbl16Class-help: The names of ViewTbl16Classes that are loaded via a class loader and added to a ViewTbl array. Use the fully qualified class names of the desired classes. Use a comma to separate multiple class name entries.
a-ViewTbl32Class-help: The names of ViewTbl32Classes that are loaded via a class loader and added to a ViewTbl array. Use the fully qualified class names of the desired classes. Use a comma to separate multiple class name entries.
a-WLDFBuiltinSystemResourceDescriptorBea: WLDF Builtin System Resource Descriptor Bean
a-WaitForAllSessionsDuringShutdown-label: Wait For All Sessions During Shutdown
a-WantTransportLayerSecurityClientAuthen: Want Transport Layer Security Client Authentication
f-WTCServer_WTCtBridgeGlobal-a-WlsErrorD: The name of the location used to store WebLogic Server JMS messages when a message cannot be redirected. If not specified, all messages not redirected are lost. If the message cannot be placed into WlsErrorDestination for any reason, an error is logged and the message is lost.
a-WorkManagerForRemoteSessionFetching-la: Work Manager For Remote Session Fetching
f-any_RemoteResource-nameHelp: Name of the remote resource mapping
